## Context

PR 61 prototype (`bin/beat-dashboard`) showed a working hourly disc grid + ticket queue panel
(stdlib-only, 496 lines). The prototype has two weaknesses:

1. Beat-log is not the primary activity signal — most work runs through the orchestrator skill
   in interactive sessions. Git commits and ticket status changes capture all modes.
2. Cost tracking (cost_usd) is irrelevant — user is on a Claude plan; dollars don't count,
   tokens/plan limits do.

This ticket builds a revised, three-view dashboard on top of the prototype.

## Actions

### View 1 — Overview (extend prototype)
- Drop cost column
- Add **Commits today** column: `git log --since=midnight --oneline | wc -l` per project
- Add **Ticket velocity** column: tickets closed this week vs. last week (from .erg Created/status)
- Add **Health pill**: green = any done beat in last 24 h, amber = only idle, red = failed/aborted
- Beat disc grid becomes collapsible secondary panel (default collapsed)
- Window selector extends to 168 h; at >48 h collapse to day-granularity with sparkline cells

### View 2 — Project drill-down (`/project/<name>`)
- Beat log table: time, outcome, ticket, duration, diagnostics; expandable raw JSON row
- Ticket list: full status, title, age, blocker chain; sorted by readiness tier then age
- STATE.md snippet: last-updated date + "Status" section as plain text
- Back link to overview

### View 3 — Blocker graph (`/blockers`)
- Cross-project SVG DAG of tickets that block other tickets
- Nodes coloured by readiness (green=ready, blue=doing, orange=blocked, grey=pending)
- Edges show dependency direction
- Surfaces "keystone" tickets blocking multiple chains across projects

### Infrastructure
- Single `bin/beat-dashboard` file, stdlib only (no external dependencies)
- Serve all three views from one HTTPServer subclass
- Auto-refresh 60 s (meta-refresh, no WebSocket)
- Projects parsed from `~/.claude/scripts/beat.sh` or `--projects PATH:PATH:...`

## Test

```bash
# Red step: verify View 2 route exists and returns 200
python - <<'EOF'
import urllib.request, subprocess, time, signal, os, sys
srv = subprocess.Popen(["python", "bin/beat-dashboard", "--no-browser",
                        "--projects", os.path.expanduser("~/.claude")])
time.sleep(1)
try:
    code = urllib.request.urlopen("http://127.0.0.1:8765/project/.claude").getcode()
    assert code == 200, f"got {code}"
    print("PASS")
finally:
    srv.send_signal(signal.SIGINT)
EOF
```

## Exit criteria

- `bash -n bin/beat-dashboard` passes (syntax clean)
- Overview loads with commits-today and ticket-velocity columns visible
- Clicking a project row navigates to `/project/<name>` drill-down
- `/blockers` renders an SVG with at least one node when any ticket has a Blocked-by header
- No external imports (stdlib only); `ruff check bin/beat-dashboard` clean
- Auto-refresh header present in HTML (`<meta http-equiv="refresh" content="60">`)
